{
  "stem": "25651.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Jewish community was also oriented towards German culture, because it was Austria-Hungary not so many years ago.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, my father-- my parents only settled in Novy Jicin because father was in the Austrian army in the barracks in Novy Jicin.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And when he got [INAUDIBLE], he stayed in the town.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My father, for example, was [NON-ENGLISH] of the community, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So since the death of the rabbi in 1924-- that was Rabbi Dr.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Mandl-- my father sort of ran the services together with the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The [NON-ENGLISH] actually took the services, but my father was senior warden.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Well, there was only one warden.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was a small community.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And my father understood the whole process of the year's conduct of services-- holidays, prayers-- he-- he knew what should be done, so there was no necessity of a rabbi.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I remember Purim services when-- I still remember Purim services when the widow, Frau Dr.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Mandl, as we called her-- I-- I still remember when she used to take us in cheder.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was about four or five.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She was supposed to teach us Hebrew but she never-- she never actually managed.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the-- the-- the thing was that this was the German Reform Synagogue.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My father-- my father's background wasn't German Reform, but he adapted himself to German Reform.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I mean, I remember, as a child, walking on Shabbat with my parents from services and almost every Saturday, my mother would nag my father about the organ in the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There was a beautiful organ which actually we-- it had-- it had pedals, so you had to pump it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And a Goy had to come and play the organ because on Saturday, it's not allowed for a Jew to play.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
